IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Examination of liaison emergence provides an initial example of a middle range synthesis of the two perspectives that dominate organizational communication research: communication climate and network analysis. Three climate factors?relational, cognitive, and motivational?are posited to determine liaison emergence. In turn, liaison emergence is crucial to the systemic processes of coordination and control.
AB  - Examination of liaison emergence provides an initial example of a middle range synthesis of the two perspectives that dominate organizational communication research: communication climate and network analysis. Three climate factors?relational, cognitive, and motivational?are posited to determine liaison emergence. In turn, liaison emergence is crucial to the systemic processes of coordination and control.
