JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 531
EP  - 542
VL  - 7
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Little systematic research has concentrated on the effects of organization development (OD) in terms of hard-criteria measures of performance and behavior. This paper assesses the impact of three classes of OD interventions based on 65 empirical studies. A typology of outcome variables is used to show how OD has affected organizational behavior. Certain classes of interventions appear to be more effective than others.
